lambing paddock
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:a fenced area where ewes can have shelter or be observed during lambing [located close to a homestead.]
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
